more this happened,

00:32:56.600 --> 00:32:58.568
the less I wanted to tell them.

00:32:58.568 --> 00:33:01.028
I was wondering if you
had any thoughts on this,

00:33:01.028 --> 00:33:04.250
like the really strong
gender socialization.

00:33:04.250 --> 00:33:06.000
THOMAS PAGE MCBEE:
Isn't it so interesting

00:33:06.000 --> 00:33:09.230
that what we're really asking
is, what kind of person

00:33:09.230 --> 00:33:10.760
is this person going to be.

00:33:10.760 --> 00:33:14.340
like we can somehow, by
knowing if the person's born

00:33:14.340 --> 00:33:16.752
with one body or another body.

00:33:16.752 --> 00:33:18.640
I agree that it's a
really troubling thing.

00:33:18.640 --> 00:33:22.300
I really like when parents
don't find out or wait.

00:33:22.300 --> 00:33:24.310
But I also think,
like all things,

00:33:24.310 --> 00:33:27.380
there's sort of a-- I think
it's overly idealistic to assume

00:33:27.380 --> 00:33:32.020
we won't put expectations on
our children or on each other,

00:33:32.020 --> 00:33:34.747
based on what gender
we think a person is.

00:33:34.747 --> 00:33:35.830
I think, of course, we do.

00:33:35.830 --> 00:33:40.030
Life is complicated and it's a
way we make sense of the world.

00:33:40.030 --> 00:33:42.651
And these are
systems of operating.

00:33:42.651 --> 00:33:44.150
Again, I think it
goes back to like,

00:33:44.150 --> 00:33:46.095
is there a way to
integrate and to understand

00:33:46.095 --> 00:33:47.085
that this is a paradox.

00:33:47.085 --> 00:33:49.330
Where on one hand,
gender is probably

00:33:49.330 --> 00:33:52.100
pretty innate for most
of us, and for all of us.

00:33:52.100 --> 00:33:53.710
And most of us
are born in a body

00:33:53.710 --> 00:33:57.010
that we don't want to change.

00:33:57.010 --> 00:34:00.050
But even so, we need
to operate in a way

00:34:00.050 --> 00:34:03.924
that we understand the cultural
and institutional expectations

00:34:03.924 --> 00:34:05.340
that come along
with those bodies.

00:34:05.340 --> 00:34:07.410
And it's very
restricting to all of us

00:34:07.410 --> 00:34:10.750
when we assume that because
somebody looks one way,

00:34:10.750 --> 00:34:13.710
therefore everything about
them is going to be this way.

00:34:13.710 --> 00:34:16.739
So I guess to me, there's
not some simple solution

00:34:16.739 --> 00:34:20.360
of like well, if we just
raise our children agendered,

00:34:20.360 --> 00:34:22.620
then somehow that will
solve our problems.

00:34:22.620 --> 00:34:23.510
I think probably not.

00:34:23.510 --> 00:34:25.218
I think probably the
best thing we can do

00:34:25.218 --> 00:34:28.199
is teach our kids that gender
is complex and nuanced.

00:34:28.199 --> 00:34:30.380
And there's no way right
way to be and encourage

00:34:30.380 --> 00:34:31.659
them to just be themselves.

00:34:31.659 --> 00:34:35.270
And model that for our
kids and for each other.

00:34:38.260 --> 00:34:39.003
Yes.

